He did not even want to talk and disappeared. Only after I called the police and threatened to block the exit, more than 30 minutes later, a supervisor came to talk to me. He said that I passed my "grace period" after my payment. This does not make ANY sense. A person can stay 1 hour plus 15 minutes for a grace period for $10. However, I stayed 52 minutes and needed to pay twice just because I followed the signs and paid before entering my car instead of paying by the gate. If I had just paid at the same time by the gate, it would be 10 dollars. But because I followed the sign and paid a few minutes earlier, I had to pay twice. This is ridiculous. He told us too bad, and that he's the manager and no one is going to give us our money back. We asked him if he put up the sign himself and he said no. He said "well did you take a picture of the sign? Do you have proof?" He was really mean to us, all over a measly $8. We are more upset over how degrading his speech was than the money itself. We are surely never parking in this parking garage again. He also refused to give our parking ticket back, and when we tried to leave he wouldn't let us out and made us back up and go around just to be rude. We felt like he basically told us to f-off. When I came back the next day and told him I only needed two days, he quickly told me that two days was $45.00 per day (the same as three).  I asked him to show me where that was posted and he could not.  He became very upset and told me to be quiet and listen to him.  I told him that I thought he was very dishonest (and a few other things) and left.  I am currently disputing this with my credit card company.

reviews.name: L D.
reviews.review:
There was a misunderstanding about me taking my car vs. needing to grab something.  When the manager found out I was simply grabbing something, he lost it on me, started yelling, told me to get out, told me my month contract was cancelled (I was only three days in), and told me to leave.  He tried to reach into my car to grab the monthly parking permit from my rear window, which I obviously need to get a refund.

A few notes- The garage was very busy and I waited for 15 minutes while they attended to other customers and grabbed my car.  I understand they were really busy, so told them not to worry, that I would park my car on the street and then return later in the evening.  This didn't keep the manager from yelling at me.  He escalated the situation, told me my contract was "cancelled".

I returned to ask for a refund for the days I wont be using.  The manager claimed he can't process the refund, that it needs to come from the management office, and that I would only get 50% back.

reviews.name: Brian W.
reviews.review:
parking lot at 5th and Howard Street has been a major public nuisance.

For example:

      ugly, rusty cyclone fence always in the need of repair,

      support poles knocked out of their cement anchors,

      fence sticking out over the sidewalk on the Tehama Street side,

      weeds growing around the entire perimeter of the lot,

      parking lot attendant kiosk covered with graffiti, and

      hanging flower baskets  promised but never delivered.

Any property improvement that did occur resulted because neighbors complained to the proper authorities, such as Public Works or the Community Benefits District about the shotty condition of the parking lot.

The people running the parking lot (and the property owners) never lifted a finger to improve the condition of that lot on their own.

It seems to me from my observation that it is done on purpose at a very loud level , pretty much all night , just being very mean and evil , this is not right . thank you and GOD Bless , I was trying to get contact with the CEO

reviews.name: Stephanie T.
reviews.review: The staff was friendly, fast and I felt totally taken care of.   The only bummer is that this part of Eddy St. is totally Tenderloin and I would not feel safe returning to the garage after dark.  Perhaps a ride hailing / taxi add on to an SF trip would make it work perfectly. I would recommend this garage with that one caveat.

reviews.name: Jeanette R.
reviews.review:
We tried this place when we found out that our hotel was charging $75.00 a day!!  we were able to park our car for a total of 3 days and it was less then 1 day at the hotel.
We will definitely use ParkMe again!!

reviews.name: Jonathan D.
reviews.review: Wanted less expensive option for morning meeting at S.F.Public. It's about 8 blocks from the library-- I don't mind walking through the Tenderloin. Did see 2 cops running & 4 cop cars (wrong way through one-way traffic) take off in pursuit of a cell phone thief. Staff was polite and efficient. Cell phone check in with reservation was easy. They had my car at the front of the lot's 1st floor at the time I said I'd return. There's a little Burmese restaurant 2 blocks away on Eddy. Had nice hot bowl of catfish chowder before picking up the car.

reviews.name: Maya Y.
reviews.review: So glad we did this. Whenever we drive up to SF, we always end up wandering around and finding either sketchy or overpriced parking. This helped make pur day much less stressful and worrisome. The attendants were friendly and helpful, and happily took us up to the 2nd story when we wanted to drop off some stuff. Thank you!

reviews.name: Edward S.
reviews.review: Worked great. I'd suggest adding a map view when the list of search results comes up to make choosing a space a little easier. Will definitely use your service again.

reviews.name: Heather J.
reviews.review:
This was my first time using ParkMe, as I was driving up to San Francisco
for an all-day meeting and wanted to find reasonably-priced parking within
a couple blocks of the conference hotel. I didn't know reservations were a
new feature, but it was super helpful to be able to plan ahead and not
scramble for parking at 7:30AM. The website helped me find several garages
that were significantly better priced than the conference hotel. All I had
to do was show my reservation at the garage, and the attendants took care
of the rest.

reviews.name: Heather J.
reviews.review: I needed a parking spot for an all-day meeting at the Hilton Union Square, and I had no interest in paying $50+ to park in the hotel garage. Rock Star Parking was just a block or two away, easy to find, and the pre-booked price was great. The garage is in the Tenderloin, so the surroundings are a bit sketchy, but the attendants were professional and the garage felt totally secure. Would recommend.

reviews.name: Stephen P.
reviews.review: Great location if you are Looking for inexpensive parking near Market Street.

reviews.name: Ben S.
reviews.review: Great lot. Great price. Great location

result.name: 530 Turk St Parking
result.note: Note that this lot is attended (valet parking), Mon-Fri; 8AM to 5PM

reviews.name: Niem T.
reviews.review: Parked three days in a row from June 2-4 for Clusterfest comedy/music festival. First two nights were fine, no problems. On the last night, there was no attendant. At 11:30 pm, I came back to the passenger rear window totally smashed, and my trunk belongings scattered around. Glass was all over my backseat. Fortunately, I had nothing of significant value in the car and nothing seemed to be stolen. It was a hassle to clean up all the class and drive back with no window in the back. I don't think I will park here again.
